          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A menu item with a view does not draw its title, state, font, or other standard drawing attributes, and assigns drawing responsibility entirely to the view. Keyboard equivalents and type-select continue to use the key equivalent and title as normal. For more details, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "Application Menu and Pop-up List Programming Topics",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Cocoa/Conceptual/MenuList/MenuList.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/10000032i"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By default, a menu item has a "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "nil"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " view."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
